What happens when you initialize a repository? Why do you need to do it?
new file ( .git ) is created , new repo. which will hold my files , its branches and update nodes will be done. to be able to back any node i wanna back to.

How is the staging area different from the working directory and the repository? What value do you think it offers?
staging area is between working directory and repository, working directory is the current folder which i am working in , repo is the done files included in.
